A look at LeBron James’ pursuit of Kareem Abdul-Jabbar for the NBA’s scoring record. Abdul-Jabbar has held the record since April 5, 1984:Abdul-Jabbar points: 38,387.James points: 38,271.Difference: 116 points.James’ latest game: He scored 41 points Saturday night in the Los Angeles Lakers’ 125-121 overtime loss at Boston.James’ scoring average this season: 30.2.Potential record-breaker: At his current rate of 30.2 points per game, with 117 points needed to pass Abdul-Jabbar, it would take James four more games to become the NBA’s scoring leader. Assuming he does not miss any games, that makes the potential record-breaking game Feb. 4 at New Orleans.Next Lakers game: Monday at Brooklyn.___AP NBA: https://apnews.com/hub/NBA and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports